<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,359,1825]" box="[264,1068,359,385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Larvae. Body length: 3.4–4.0 mm. Caudal filaments length: 1.4 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,359,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Head yellow­brown, with no distinct color pattern. Ocelli dark brown. Labrum (Fig. 
<number box="[1297,1310,399,425]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
) with anterior margin with median row of robust, branched setae, followed laterally by fine and long simple setae; dorsal surface with three submarginal fine, long, simple setae on each side of midline, and one pair of fine, long, simple setae on each side of midline, located more posteriorly. Hypopharynx as in Figure 
<number box="[892,909,559,585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
. Left mandible (Fig. 
<number box="[1165,1180,559,585]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
) with outer and inner set of incisors respectively with four and two denticles; prostheca robust; triangular process at base of mola well developed. Right mandible (Fig. 
<number box="[1055,1071,639,665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
) with outer and inner set of incisors respectively with three and four denticles; prostheca bifid, relatively well developed. Maxillae (Fig. 
<number box="[578,593,719,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0">5</number>
) with robust, spiniform seta on medial hump; palps two­segmented; palpifer relatively long; segment 
<number box="[755,770,759,785]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
nearly 0.5x length of segment 
<number box="[1136,1152,759,785]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
. Labium (Fig. 
<number box="[264,279,799,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.0">6</number>
) with glossae with four to five short, fine, simple setae medially, and two to three long, fine, apically branched setae distally; dorsum of paraglossae with apical row of long, fine, apically branched setae, and ventrally with a group of three short, fine, simple setae; segment 
<number box="[330,345,919,945]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
of labial palp with rounded distomedial process, inner margin with long, fine, simple setae, and dorsally with two long, fine, simple setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,359,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Thorax yellow­brown, except for the tips of the fore wing pads, medium brown; without distinct pattern. 
<collectingCountry box="[509,567,1039,1065]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing pads absent. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[881,1011,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Figs. 
<number box="[951,1011,1039,1065]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
</figureCitation>
) pale yellow­brown; fore femora (
<figureCitation box="[367,441,1079,1105]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[426,441,1079,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) broader than others, with submedial row of long, robust, simple setae, increasing in size ventrally; dorsally with row of short to long, robust, simple setae; anterior half of ventral margin with long, robust, simple setae, and short and stout simple setae; mid femur (
<figureCitation box="[408,481,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[466,481,1199,1225]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterior row of long, robust, simple setae; hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1316,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1286,1316,1199,1225]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) with relatively few setae; tibia and tarsi almost bare, except for a few short, fine, simple setae dorsally, and a few short, stout, simple setae ventrally; tarsal claws (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1197,1279,1305]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1182,1197,1279,1305]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) with four to five denticles on lateral and medial margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,359,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Abdomen pale yellow­brown, except for segments 
<number box="[920,968,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.7">2, 7</number>
, and 
<number box="[1033,1049,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="8.0">8</number>
, medium brown; without distinct pattern. Terga (
<figureCitation box="[583,667,1399,1425]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[638,667,1399,1425]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior triangular spines absent in segments 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1– 3</number>
, segments 
<number box="[412,457,1439,1465]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
with triangular spines restricted laterally, and segments 
<number box="[1128,1187,1439,1465]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
with triangular spines along the posterior margin. Gills as in 
<figureCitation box="[871,988,1479,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Figure 
<number box="[956,988,1479,1505]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
, whitish and weakly tracheated. Paraproct (
<figureCitation box="[455,540,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[266,1272,803,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[209,1378,787,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Varipes helenae, sp. n., nymph. 7. Foreleg. 8. Detail of tarsal claw. 9. Mid femur. 10. Hind femur. 11. Tergum 4 (detail of posterior margin). 12. Gill 4. 13. Paraproct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157946/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[510,540,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) marginally with six to seven spines. Caudal filaments whitish. Adults. Unknown.
</paragraph>
